cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.SY, cs.MM

The paper discusses safety challenges and solutions in mobile social networks, which involve the intersection of several computer science subfields. The most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) since the paper focuses on the characteristics and challenges of mobile networks. The second likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) since the paper discusses security, privacy, and trust issues in MSNs. The third likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) since the paper discusses the characteristics of social networks and their integration with mobile networks. The fourth likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control) since the paper discusses the design and implementation of safety solutions in MSNs. The fifth likely category is cs.MM (Multimedia) since the paper discusses the sharing and distribution of data objects in MSNs.
